Give a lady a hand.

17:26.921 --> 17:28.130
Ooh. Why?

17:28.631 --> 17:29.924
How can I help you?

17:30.341 --> 17:32.009
I'm looking for Patty Bladell.

17:32.093 --> 17:33.010
Well...

17:33.427 --> 17:35.555
you upgraded and...

17:36.430 --> 17:38.182
I happen to have a thing...

17:38.933 --> 17:40.393
for younger men.

17:43.646 --> 17:47.066
- Hey, that's my girlfriends bracelet.
- No, it's mine.

17:47.149 --> 17:50.361
Bullshit. It has a GPS tracking chip
that I used to find her here.

17:50.444 --> 17:53.906
That is pretty intense
Stalker, Texas Ranger.

17:53.990 --> 17:55.324
I'm not a stalker.

17:56.033 --> 17:59.745
I need to know where she is at all times,
at least until she takes me back.

17:59.829 --> 18:01.831
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
I'm not judging.

18:01.914 --> 18:03.082
Everyone has their quirks.

18:03.624 --> 18:06.127
You stalk, I'm a terrible person.

18:06.210 --> 18:10.673
Plus, I appreciate someone
who won't take no for an answer.

18:11.257 --> 18:14.385
But I'm telling you,
you're going about this the wrong way.

18:14.844 --> 18:15.720
What do you mean?

18:15.803 --> 18:18.347
Winners win at any cost.

18:18.806 --> 18:21.767
You need to be willling to go
to an alliance to get what you want.

18:21.851 --> 18:24.353
Hello. I tried putting
a tracking device on her.

18:24.437 --> 18:26.314
I'm pretty sure
that's going to any lengths.

18:26.397 --> 18:29.900
You're sitting on the sidelines.
You need to get in the game, son.

18:29.984 --> 18:32.903
You need a grand, romantic gesture.

18:32.987 --> 18:35.656
Oh, like the boom box in <i>Say Anything.</i>

18:36.365 --> 18:37.199
Look...

18:37.700 --> 18:42.288
just figure out what Patty wants
more than anything in the world

18:42.663 --> 18:45.958
and you figure a way to give it to her.

18:46.042 --> 18:49.337
Can't believe I'm taking life tips
from someone who lives in a cardboard box,

18:49.420 --> 18:51.839
but good advice is good advice.

18:51.922 --> 18:54.717
I can't believe baby Jesus
sent me a hot teen werewolf, so...

18:58.888 --> 19:02.850
<i>I have been kidnapped
by the same people twice in one day.</i>

19:02.933 --> 19:05.394
<i>It was a perfect metaphor for my life.</i>

19:05.478 --> 19:09.815
<i>Every time I thought I made progress,
I ended up in exactly the same spot.</i>

19:09.899 --> 19:12.068
Don't count on those hunters
coming to your rescue.

19:12.443 --> 19:15.112
After your litle stunt,
we moved this truck so far away

19:15.196 --> 19:17.531
even my bloodhounds
couldn't sniff you out.

19:19.241 --> 19:20.743
She's not going anywhere.

19:21.369 --> 19:24.163
Let's go, Momma.
Time to lower the boom on Bob.

19:24.246 --> 19:25.831
Why are you helping her?

19:25.915 --> 19:27.375
What did Bob ever do to you?

19:27.458 --> 19:29.460
Other than being the reason
I grew up in foster care?

19:30.378 --> 19:32.004
What did he have to do with that?

19:32.505 --> 19:36.926
I was too devastated over losing him
to raise a child.

19:37.301 --> 19:39.178
Because you got dumped?

19:40.012 --> 19:42.181
Wow, you're crazier than you look.

19:42.264 --> 19:44.016
I'm not crazy.

19:47.645 --> 19:49.188
Another text from Nonnie.

19:49.271 --> 19:51.524
She and a guy named Christian
have sent her like a million.

19:51.607 --> 19:54.360
Text her back. If she don't answer,
they'll get suspicious.

19:57.446 --> 20:00.157
"Sorry I ghosted.

20:00.574 --> 20:02.451
Laying low.

20:03.160 --> 20:06.831
Freaking out about the competition."

20:09.625 --> 20:13.546
Later loser. Next time I see you,
I'll have a crown on my head.

20:28.436 --> 20:31.439
<i>I thought if I lost weight,
I'd have a fresh start.</i>

20:31.731 --> 20:34.608
<i>If people liked me, if I had a boyfriend,</i>

20:34.692 --> 20:35.943
<i>if I got the crown,</i>

20:36.360 --> 20:37.778
<i>but none of it mattered.</i>

20:37.862 --> 20:40.156
<i>It was always the same story,</i>

20:40.489 --> 20:44.076
<i>which meant I couldn't save Bob
and I couldn't save myself.</i>

20:44.869 --> 20:45.911
<i>Roxy was right.</i>

20:46.245 --> 20:47.496
<i>I was a loser.</i>

20:47.872 --> 20:48.873
<i>Always had been.</i>

20:49.707 --> 20:51.917
<i>Call it a curse. Call it bad luck.</i>

20:52.126 --> 20:53.210
<i>Call it fate.</i>

20:53.586 --> 20:55.838
<i>No wonder bad things kept happening to me.</i>

20:56.380 --> 20:58.257
<i>Bladell women never win.</i>

21:06.849 --> 21:09.185
Hey. I need you to hook me up.

21:09.268 --> 21:11.020
Why? I heard you got clean.

21:11.395 --> 21:12.271
I did.

21:12.354 --> 21:13.606
I mean, I am.

21:15.900 --> 21:20.529
My dad won't let me compete at Regionals
because he thinks pageants are a trigger.

21:20.613 --> 21:22.281
You know what's really a trigger?

21:22.740 --> 21:25.868
Him letting my secret half-sister
be in pageants instead of me.

21:27.453 --> 21:31.207
I wanted him to make things right
with her, not replace me with her.

21:31.999 --> 21:35.085
Fuck him.
He's clearly doing what he wants to do.

21:35.878 --> 21:36.712
Why don't you?

21:38.798 --> 21:39.632
You're right.

21:40.674 --> 21:42.468
I'm gonna go over to registration,

21:42.551 --> 21:44.178
I'm gonna sign up for Regionals,

21:44.261 --> 21:46.514
and I'm gonna kick Roxy's ass.

21:48.057 --> 21:49.767
You sound pretty sure of yourself.

21:50.267 --> 21:51.977
Not worried about the competition?

21:52.728 --> 21:54.772
I am the competition.

21:56.065 --> 21:57.399
I've never lost a pageant,

21:58.150 --> 21:59.026
and I never will.

22:00.861 --> 22:02.279
Need a ride to registration?

22:06.200 --> 22:09.578
<i>I had spent so much
of my life feeling like a loser,</i>

22:09.870 --> 22:13.624
<i>but that day,
I felt like I had won at life.</i>

22:14.041 --> 22:15.084
<i>We had the cake.</i>

22:15.584 --> 22:16.585
<i>We ate it,</i>

22:16.836 --> 22:18.712
<i>and it was more than just sex.</i>

22:18.796 --> 22:21.131
<i>We had shared real intimacy.</i>

22:27.930 --> 22:29.932
- Oh, no, no.
- No.

22:30.015 --> 22:33.811
You may be able to ignore your dad,
but I can't.

22:34.144 --> 22:35.896
Supposed to have a meeting later.

22:38.232 --> 22:42.361
Something tells me he's gonna strip me
of my senior partnership.

22:43.070 --> 22:44.113
I gotta go.

22:44.738 --> 22:46.740
Try not to have too much fun without me.

22:53.706 --> 22:54.999
So?

22:56.083 --> 22:57.042
What do you think?

22:59.044 --> 22:59.879
Well...

23:01.797 --> 23:02.798
it was weird,

23:03.757 --> 23:04.675
and crazy,

23:06.010 --> 23:10.389
and there were a lot of arms, and legs,
and beards.

23:10.973 --> 23:12.558
But did you like it?

23:16.312 --> 23:17.271
I loved it.

23:21.483 --> 23:25.779
Maybe it was everything
I never knew I always wanted.

23:35.289 --> 23:38.417
Who knew this would be the next phase
in our marriage.

23:39.084 --> 23:41.587
- A thruple?
- I know.

23:41.670 --> 23:44.298
There's so much to work out.
Where we're gonna live.

23:44.381 --> 23:46.342
What we tell the kids.

23:47.176 --> 23:48.218
Oh, ugh.

23:48.552 --> 23:51.305
Roxy has a huge zit on her face.

23:52.056 --> 23:55.517
I have to do a pre-pageant
skin-tervention asap.

23:56.560 --> 23:58.395
Well, go. We'll catch up later.

24:00.606 --> 24:01.941
Gotta shower first.

24:03.192 --> 24:05.361
Can't have me coaching
looking thoroughly three-wayed.

24:05.444 --> 24:06.278
Bob?

24:09.198 --> 24:10.449
I really do love you.

24:11.283 --> 24:13.077
I really, really love you.

24:17.998 --> 24:20.918
<i>They always say
good things come in threes.</i>

24:21.335 --> 24:23.671
<i>I had Coralee, I had Bob.</i>

24:24.129 --> 24:27.341
<i>All that was left
was Roxy winning Regionals.</i>

24:29.551 --> 24:30.386
Hi, Bob.

24:31.512 --> 24:33.764
What are you doing here?

24:35.099 --> 24:38.560
Did you really think that Roxy was gonna
leave me for you two hole punchers?

24:38.644 --> 24:40.354
What? I don't understand.

24:40.437 --> 24:42.940
Your services as her coach
are no longer required.

24:44.692 --> 24:46.026
Actually, they never were.

24:46.944 --> 24:47.820
We played you.

24:50.114 --> 24:53.492
I wanted you to think that you were
finally gonna get everything you wanted.

24:53.575 --> 24:56.537
To finally know what it felt like
to be a winner,

24:56.620 --> 24:58.622
coaching a real champion,

24:58.706 --> 25:01.041
only to have it all ripped away...

25:01.917 --> 25:03.335
by me.

25:03.419 --> 25:04.420
That's sick.

25:05.129 --> 25:06.171
You are sick.

25:06.880 --> 25:08.090
Oh, you have no idea.

25:08.674 --> 25:12.511
So, how does it feel
to be left out in the cold?

25:16.932 --> 25:18.225
Actually, it feels fine.

25:21.520 --> 25:23.355
What do you mean, it feels fine?

25:23.689 --> 25:27.401
I just told you
your pageant dreams are over,

25:27.484 --> 25:29.903
and you can't go running back to Patty.

25:30.195 --> 25:31.155
I don't care.

25:33.115 --> 25:36.493
And believe me,
no one is more surprised than me.

25:37.578 --> 25:41.040
Pageants are your drug of choice.
They're the most important thing to you.

25:41.123 --> 25:41.957
I guess...

25:42.916 --> 25:44.418
I guess not any more.

25:49.673 --> 25:50.924
I don't understand.

25:51.300 --> 25:52.134
I know.

25:53.010 --> 25:58.515
You'll never understand what it feels like
to be loved this completely.

25:58.974 --> 26:00.434
To feel this satisfied.

26:01.685 --> 26:03.062
What are you talking about?

26:03.479 --> 26:05.731
Because you think love
is a zero sum game,

26:06.732 --> 26:09.151
and that is why you will always be alone.

26:10.402 --> 26:12.321
Don't you dare judge me...

26:13.113 --> 26:14.948
after everything you put me through.

26:17.201 --> 26:19.036
I will never...

26:19.745 --> 26:21.038
let you be happy.

26:22.247 --> 26:24.625
I will never let you win.

26:25.084 --> 26:26.335
I already have.

26:38.889 --> 26:40.015
Stella Rose...

26:42.684 --> 26:43.602
are you okay?

26:44.186 --> 26:45.270
No, definitely not.

26:46.063 --> 26:48.065
But I will be once I'm through with you.

26:49.817 --> 26:50.859
What are you gonna do?

26:51.652 --> 26:54.279
Well, a bit of a change of plans.

26:54.738 --> 26:56.824
I was just gonna let Bob think
he could have Roxy

26:56.907 --> 26:58.867
and then rip away his pageant dreams,

26:58.951 --> 27:02.121
but I... I had to make sure
he wouldn't go running back to you.

27:02.412 --> 27:05.082
- I-I don't understand.
- And that's why we grabbed you.

27:05.541 --> 27:06.875
Take away his plan B.

27:08.085 --> 27:10.337
But now, I'm gonna make sure

27:10.420 --> 27:14.466
that he is never happy
about anything ever again.

27:14.967 --> 27:15.843
What do you mean?

27:19.221 --> 27:20.305
I'm gonna kill you...

27:21.431 --> 27:24.393
and make it look like
you took yourself out because of him.

27:24.476 --> 27:26.770
I'm gonna rig this hose
to the exhaust pipe.

27:26.854 --> 27:28.313
You'll die of asphyxiation.

27:29.189 --> 27:30.149
You're insane.

27:30.232 --> 27:31.733
You know, I-I-I-I wasn't.

27:32.234 --> 27:35.028
I spent a year in a psycho ward
and I was fine.

27:35.487 --> 27:37.489
But then Bob came back into my life...

27:38.323 --> 27:39.825
because of you, and...

27:42.077 --> 27:42.911
it all just...

27:45.038 --> 27:46.206
came flooding back.

27:48.333 --> 27:49.877
And now he's gotta pay.

27:51.170 --> 27:53.130
Bob will blame himself for your death.

27:54.548 --> 27:55.799
And he'll never get over it.

27:56.466 --> 27:58.177
My best friend, her dad is a cop.

27:58.468 --> 28:00.554
- You'll never get away with this.
- I will.

28:02.139 --> 28:07.561
Because your suicide note
is gonna be very, very convincing.

28:08.228 --> 28:12.316
Now, you make sure you get this verbatim.

28:15.110 --> 28:17.613
"Dear Bob, I thought you loved me..."

28:17.696 --> 28:19.239
Why aren't you writing?

28:19.323 --> 28:20.532
I don't want to.

28:20.991 --> 28:23.577
Do it or I'll put your face in the fryer!

28:33.420 --> 28:34.296
"Dear Bob,

28:36.173 --> 28:37.925
I thought you loved me.

28:39.384 --> 28:41.386
I thought you were my role model,

28:42.137 --> 28:43.722
a father figure

28:45.849 --> 28:48.352
and that maybe one day, even more,

28:48.435 --> 28:49.561
but now I know...

28:51.188 --> 28:52.648
it's never gonna happen...

28:54.441 --> 28:55.901
since you abandoned me.

28:56.735 --> 28:58.111
And I don't blame you

28:59.404 --> 29:01.240
because I'm a loser...

29:02.658 --> 29:05.035
and I don't deserve to live."

29:10.749 --> 29:12.626
What are... what are you doing?

29:13.043 --> 29:14.002
Painting a picture.

29:14.336 --> 29:16.088
Suicide was your last resort,

29:16.922 --> 29:20.968
but first, you turned
to the only friend you ever had.

29:21.885 --> 29:23.262
A fudge weiner.

29:25.597 --> 29:28.934
And when you couldn't numb the feelings
with the food,

29:29.309 --> 29:31.311
you took your own life.

29:32.896 --> 29:34.022
Mmm-mmm.

29:34.106 --> 29:36.692
No, that's not who I am.
That's not who I am anymore.

29:37.234 --> 29:38.193
Bullshit.

29:38.652 --> 29:41.446
You'll always be Fatty Patty.

29:42.114 --> 29:43.156
That's your legacy.

29:48.870 --> 29:51.164
<i>I had never heard it said out loud</i>

29:51.248 --> 29:53.583
<i>or seen it written down all at once.</i>

29:54.501 --> 29:56.545
<i>The suicide note I was writing,</i>

29:56.628 --> 29:58.297
<i>the picture Stella Rose was painting,</i>

29:59.131 --> 30:01.633
<i>that was a story
I'd been told my whole life.</i>

30:04.344 --> 30:05.178
Here.

30:06.722 --> 30:07.723
Enjoy it.

30:07.806 --> 30:08.849
Mmm-mmm.

30:08.932 --> 30:10.934
It'll be your last meal.

30:13.770 --> 30:15.063
<i>Bon appÃ©tit...</i>

30:16.648 --> 30:17.733
Fatty Patty.

30:21.486 --> 30:25.115
<i>But that's when I realized,
it was only true if I believed it.</i>

30:25.866 --> 30:29.578
<i>Bad things would only keep happening to me
if I thought that's what I deserved.</i>

30:37.919 --> 30:40.047
<i>It was time to write my own story.</i>

30:40.547 --> 30:42.799
<i>I wasn't a loser when I was fat,</i>

30:43.216 --> 30:44.760
<i>and I wasn't a loser now.</i>

30:45.635 --> 30:46.595
<i>I was a winner,</i>

30:47.012 --> 30:48.430
<i>and winners win.</i>

30:48.889 --> 30:49.848
<i>Period.</i>

31:11.078 --> 31:13.372
<i>Stella Rose only had it half right.</i>

31:15.165 --> 31:18.877
<i>Food had been my only friend,
but now it saved my life.</i>

31:19.127 --> 31:22.130
<i>Besides, she was the least
of my concerns now.</i>

31:22.381 --> 31:23.548
<i>I was a winner,</i>

31:23.632 --> 31:26.510
<i>and I got to Regionals registration
just in time to prove it.</i>

31:30.347 --> 31:31.973
Hi. Patty Bladell.

31:32.057 --> 31:33.183
Miss Magic Jesus.

31:38.897 --> 31:42.150
Oh, my God, you're alive,

31:42.234 --> 31:43.068
and sticky.

31:43.151 --> 31:44.027
Sorry.

31:44.694 --> 31:46.154
How'd you guys know I would be here?

31:46.238 --> 31:48.198
Nonnie's dad put a BOLO out
on the wiener mobile.

31:48.281 --> 31:50.075
You know, the one that you stole.

31:50.700 --> 31:53.453
I'm sorry. It's a long story.

31:56.706 --> 31:57.999
I can explain more later.

31:58.083 --> 31:59.626
Wait, wait. Where are you going?

31:59.709 --> 32:02.546
Magnolia says she has something
that'll help me win Regionals.

32:02.629 --> 32:04.548
- Why would she want to do that?
- I have no idea.

32:04.631 --> 32:07.759
But at this point,
I could use all the help I can get.

32:08.385 --> 32:10.053
I'm gonna call you later, okay?

32:10.470 --> 32:12.597
But my dad's truck?

32:12.681 --> 32:13.515
Okay.

32:15.892 --> 32:17.310
- Good?
- Mm-hmm.

32:17.936 --> 32:19.312
Ooh!

32:19.396 --> 32:20.230
Uh...

32:20.480 --> 32:21.648
What's all this?

32:21.731 --> 32:25.944
We thought it would be fun
to cook you dinner.

32:26.027 --> 32:29.448
And I have great news.
I got my first investor for Tampazzle.

32:29.531 --> 32:32.159
And how'd it go with my dad.
Are you still senior partner?

32:32.242 --> 32:33.452
I need to talk to you...

32:34.202 --> 32:35.078
alone.

32:37.038 --> 32:37.873
What's up?

32:38.665 --> 32:41.418
Well, it really is
just between you and me, so...

32:41.501 --> 32:42.419
Well...

32:43.211 --> 32:45.672
The only way this is gonna work
for all three of us,

32:45.755 --> 32:49.092
we... we can't keep secrets
from each other anymore.

32:49.176 --> 32:50.469
I-I agree.

32:50.552 --> 32:54.222
I mean, any good relationship
is built on the foundation of trust.

32:54.306 --> 32:57.809
Hold on. What exactly do you guys think
is going on here?

32:58.268 --> 32:59.936
- What?
- What do you mean?

33:00.312 --> 33:04.649
It's what we talked about,
the three of us together, like a thruple.

33:04.733 --> 33:05.775
A what?

33:05.859 --> 33:08.612
Uh, like a couple, but with three.

33:08.695 --> 33:11.281
No, I never agreed
to be in a relationship.

33:11.364 --> 33:13.909
I just figured the three of us
would have sex sometimes

33:13.992 --> 33:15.327
so you didn't feel left out.

33:17.871 --> 33:19.456
So I didn't feel left out?

33:19.539 --> 33:20.999
What... what is wrong with that?

33:21.082 --> 33:25.837
Well, it kind of sounds
like you were taking one for the team.

33:25.921 --> 33:29.966
Well, I told you I was gay emotionally.

33:30.050 --> 33:31.092
Oh, my God.

33:31.176 --> 33:33.345
Oh, my God,
I knew this was a terrible idea.

33:33.428 --> 33:34.596
No, no. It wasn't.

33:34.679 --> 33:36.223
I will not be a sex toy.

33:36.306 --> 33:38.141
- You're not. You weren't. You're not.
- Okay.

33:38.225 --> 33:40.727
And I will not be the third wheel
in my own marriage.

33:40.810 --> 33:42.479
That is not what he is saying.

33:42.562 --> 33:44.272
Well, that is kind of what I'm saying.

33:46.483 --> 33:48.276
No. No. No.

33:48.652 --> 33:52.113
It doesn't work
if it's not all three of us.

33:52.197 --> 33:55.825
For you, Bob, for you.
But it works for me if it's just us.

33:56.326 --> 33:59.621
Look, I just gave up
my entire political career for you.

34:00.121 --> 34:01.331
What are you talking about?

34:01.414 --> 34:03.959
That's what I wanted to tell you
in private.

34:05.460 --> 34:08.755
Your dad said he'd back my campaign
for Mayor,

34:09.214 --> 34:11.550
but only if I broke up with you.

34:12.384 --> 34:13.552
He what?

34:13.717 --> 34:14.553
Yeah.

34:14.969 --> 34:18.514
He said he didn't want his gay son
in the public eye

34:18.598 --> 34:21.016
and that it was a small price to pay

34:21.101 --> 34:23.812
for me to get what I always wanted.

34:24.813 --> 34:28.733
Except what I really always wanted
was you.

34:31.570 --> 34:34.281
I picked you Bob,

34:34.906 --> 34:37.324
and now, I need you to pick me too.

34:39.202 --> 34:41.663
You need me. But...

34:41.746 --> 34:42.789
He's right, Bob.

34:43.873 --> 34:45.708
This isn't fair on either one of us.

34:45.792 --> 34:47.960
No, no, no. But... but you... you said...

34:48.043 --> 34:49.588
I said I would try.

34:49.670 --> 34:52.507
And we barely tried, and it was...

34:54.009 --> 34:55.092
so good.

34:55.176 --> 34:56.261
We... we...

34:56.344 --> 34:57.721
we had fun.

34:57.804 --> 35:00.974
We had great sex. We were connected.

35:01.057 --> 35:02.684
It was... we had everything.

35:06.021 --> 35:06.855
Bob.

35:07.647 --> 35:08.815
It's not gonna work.

35:11.192 --> 35:12.277
It's time to choose.

35:13.194 --> 35:14.279
