35:16.156 --> 35:17.157
if I choose,

35:18.700 --> 35:19.951
either way I lose.

35:21.244 --> 35:22.078
Well...

35:23.121 --> 35:25.457
if you don't choose,
you're gonna lose us both.

35:40.889 --> 35:41.806
Magnolia?

35:47.062 --> 35:48.146
Hey, beautiful.

35:50.148 --> 35:51.441
What are you doing here?

35:51.524 --> 35:53.360
I was supposed to meet Magnolia.

35:54.152 --> 35:55.028
I know.

35:56.112 --> 35:56.946
Come here.

36:09.334 --> 36:10.335
Christian?

36:11.878 --> 36:14.339
- What did you do?
- It's a grand, romantic gesture.

36:14.964 --> 36:18.551
You said you were worried about
the competition, so I took care of it.

36:19.052 --> 36:20.804
Magnolia doesn't even do pageants anymore.

36:20.887 --> 36:24.140
She is. She went back
and she never loses. So...

36:29.396 --> 36:30.397
Is she...

36:32.190 --> 36:33.024
dead?

36:33.108 --> 36:36.069
Not yet.
I just roofied her and kidnapped her.

36:36.778 --> 36:38.113
What do you mean, not yet?

36:39.155 --> 36:40.073
I figured...

36:41.449 --> 36:43.034
we could do that part together.

36:46.162 --> 36:48.248
What makes you think that I would ever...

36:48.331 --> 36:50.083
You said you wanted to be a winner,

36:50.417 --> 36:52.502
and winners win at any cost.

36:53.002 --> 36:54.671
I didn't mean this.

36:55.755 --> 36:59.134
- What are you doing?
- What kind of person would kidnap someone?

37:04.806 --> 37:05.640
What?

37:07.934 --> 37:09.144
Me. I-I would.

37:09.227 --> 37:11.354
I would kidnap someone. I tried.

37:11.438 --> 37:12.605
What are you talking about?

37:12.689 --> 37:15.442
I tried. I tried to kidnap Roxy,
my biggest competition.

37:15.525 --> 37:17.485
See? We are the same.

37:17.694 --> 37:21.156
The only thing that stopped me
was that I was kidnapped first.

37:21.531 --> 37:24.284
You... What? How'd you get away?

37:28.788 --> 37:30.206
I did some pretty dark shit.

37:32.667 --> 37:33.501
Great.

37:34.335 --> 37:35.587
So, let's do some more.

37:44.637 --> 37:46.389
- You want me to...
- Kill her.

37:47.766 --> 37:49.476
- No.
- Yes.

37:50.143 --> 37:52.187
You said it yourself. There's no demon.

37:53.146 --> 37:55.023
That everything bad you've ever done,

37:55.607 --> 37:56.649
it's just you.

37:57.859 --> 37:59.402
That doesn't make me a killer.

37:59.486 --> 38:01.780
Why not? We killed that homeless guy.

38:03.865 --> 38:04.824
This isn't the same.

38:04.908 --> 38:06.576
Stop fighting it.

38:07.368 --> 38:08.578
Embrace it.

38:08.953 --> 38:10.079
Be the demon.

38:11.498 --> 38:12.332
Patty?

38:13.458 --> 38:14.709
Patty, what's happening?

38:16.252 --> 38:17.921
<i>I didn't know what was happening.</i>

38:18.004 --> 38:19.881
<i>Could Christian be right about me?</i>

38:20.131 --> 38:23.218
<i>Was this what it meant to be a winner
at any cost?</i>

38:23.843 --> 38:25.929
<i>Maybe I still had my story all wrong.</i>

38:26.429 --> 38:29.474
<i>Maybe I did deserve all the bad things
that happened to me.</i>

38:29.808 --> 38:33.728
<i>Not because I was a loser,
but because I was just bad.</i>

38:34.521 --> 38:36.731
Patty, do it now. She's seen us.
You have to.

38:36.815 --> 38:38.399
- Do what?
- Patty, now.

38:38.775 --> 38:40.068
Do it or I will.

38:40.401 --> 38:41.486
No!

38:42.946 --> 38:43.780
Ow.

38:43.863 --> 38:45.198
Magnolia, run.

38:49.786 --> 38:50.703
You idiot.

38:51.329 --> 38:54.332
She'll go to the police.
We'll both go to jail.

38:54.415 --> 38:55.542
I was protecting her.

38:55.625 --> 38:58.336
You think that makes you what, a hero?

38:58.628 --> 38:59.629
You're the villain.

39:00.380 --> 39:02.549
- No, I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

39:03.049 --> 39:06.344
Every time you try to do something good,
you fuck it up.

39:06.427 --> 39:08.972
- That's not true.
- You pushed Dixie off a truck.

39:09.556 --> 39:11.933
- You dumped her out of a wheelchair.
- Stop.

39:12.016 --> 39:12.976
You ruined Bob's life.

39:13.059 --> 39:14.602
- Tried to kidnap Roxy...
- Stop talking.

39:14.686 --> 39:16.104
- And you would have...
- Stop talking.

39:16.187 --> 39:17.021
Face it.

39:17.522 --> 39:18.773
You're a bad person.

39:18.857 --> 39:21.150
I'm a good person! I'm a good person!

39:21.234 --> 39:23.319
- Patty. Stop.
- I'm a good person.

39:23.403 --> 39:24.821
- Patty?
- I'm a good person.

39:24.904 --> 39:26.281
I'm a good person.

39:26.698 --> 39:27.991
I'm a good person.

39:28.575 --> 39:29.701
I'm a good person.

39:30.159 --> 39:31.160
I'm a good person.

39:31.536 --> 39:32.745
I'm a good person.

39:32.829 --> 39:34.372
I'm a good person.

39:34.455 --> 39:35.748
I'm a good person.

39:51.973 --> 39:54.976
<i>They had asked me
to choose, but how could I?</i>

39:55.518 --> 39:58.396
<i>For me, it was an impossible choice.</i>

39:58.730 --> 40:00.940
<i>I had tasted true happiness, and then...</i>

40:01.649 --> 40:02.984
<i>poof, it was gone.</i>

40:03.484 --> 40:04.736
<i>And now I had nothing.</i>

40:05.570 --> 40:08.031
<i>No pageant winner, no Bob,</i>

40:08.489 --> 40:09.574
<i>no Coralee.</i>

40:10.283 --> 40:11.993
<i>I was destined to die alone.</i>

40:21.961 --> 40:25.131
<i>But Patty Bladell had other plans.</i>

40:40.563 --> 40:43.733
Thank you for coming. I'm so sorry,
I didn't know who else to call.

40:44.567 --> 40:45.777
Patty, what happened?

40:51.282 --> 40:52.325
Oh, my God!

40:54.327 --> 40:57.455
Okay. Please. Bob, you have to help me.

41:02.877 --> 41:06.714
Tell me exactly what happened.

41:12.929 --> 41:15.556
We are not calling the police. We can't.

41:15.640 --> 41:18.351
Why not? It was self-defense.
He was dangerous.

41:18.434 --> 41:21.938
Only after the first few blows.
You must have hit him, like, 37 times.

41:22.271 --> 41:23.147
Oh, my God.

41:24.107 --> 41:25.483
You think I'm a murderer.

41:25.566 --> 41:26.859
No, I didn't say that.

41:26.943 --> 41:28.444
I'm a bad person. I am a bad person.

41:28.528 --> 41:30.947
- I'm... I'm worse than bad.
- Patty? Calm down.

41:31.030 --> 41:33.366
I don't even know why you're here.
I ruined your life.

41:33.449 --> 41:34.826
'Cause you also saved it.

41:37.954 --> 41:39.414
What are you talking about?

41:42.875 --> 41:46.254
I was gonna kill myself
when you called tonight.

41:46.587 --> 41:47.672
Oh, my God. Bob.

41:47.755 --> 41:50.633
And it is the second time it has happened.

41:51.384 --> 41:54.053
The first time, when you called
to say you wanted to do pageants,

41:54.137 --> 41:56.180
I had a gun in my mouth then, too.

41:57.932 --> 41:59.851
I never much believed in destiny,

42:01.477 --> 42:03.479
but I am starting to think you and I,

42:04.981 --> 42:06.065
we're fated.

42:08.860 --> 42:10.236
I feel that way too.

42:11.654 --> 42:13.156
You saved my life.

42:14.240 --> 42:15.074
Twice.

42:16.034 --> 42:18.161
Now I am going to save yours.

42:20.121 --> 42:21.205
Whoa, whoa!

42:21.914 --> 42:23.041
Take off your clothes.

42:24.375 --> 42:25.209
Now?

42:26.169 --> 42:28.212
Is this some kind of turn on for you?

42:28.296 --> 42:30.715
No, they are covered in blood.
We gotta get rid of 'em.

42:30.798 --> 42:33.009
Come. I've got something
you can wear in the car.

43:18.805 --> 43:20.056
What the fuck?

43:20.807 --> 43:24.018
What the fuck?

43:24.102 --> 43:25.728
Stop screaming. Someone might hear you.

43:27.897 --> 43:30.650
This has been the worst day ever!

43:30.733 --> 43:32.860
I tell you, I should have killed myself!

43:33.236 --> 43:37.240
Otherwise what else
could possibly go wrong?

43:40.201 --> 43:41.035
Well...

43:44.789 --> 43:46.707
I may have...

43:48.209 --> 43:49.085
also...

43:49.961 --> 43:50.962
sort of...

43:51.796 --> 43:53.172
killed Stella Rose.

